## Hints for Future Agents
- Cleanup runs AT STARTUP of Claude Code, not continuously: session files
  older than cleanupPeriodDays are deleted when the CLI launches.
- The same setting also gates automatic removal of orphaned subagent
  worktrees at startup (per https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees).
- It controls retention only, not whether transcripts are written
  (that's CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_PROMPT_HISTORY / --no-session-persistence).
- This repo's claude_settings.json must sync to ~/.claude/settings.json
  (symlink or copy step) before the change takes effect.
- The marketplace-swap + fastMode-removal changes in claude_settings.json
  and the codex_config.toml trust entry were deliberately LEFT UNCOMMITTED
  — the user only asked for the cleanupPeriodDays change. Don't assume
  they were forgotten; they predate this session.

